INSERT INTO places VALUES(543,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/news/50-new-bangkok-restaurants-opened-2024-you-to-check-out#30','<article>Kwann</article>','2025-09-08 04:22:21.374277',13.745791299999998713,100.55788360000001979,'73/7-8, Soi Sukhumvit 13, Khwaeng Khlong Toei Nuea, Watthana, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10110, Thailand','ChIJG3PhKLKf4jARylYRZrcVwxo','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJG3PhKLKf4jARylYRZrcVwxo','Kwann','Restaurant','Chef Napol “Joe”Jantraget, acclaimed for the local Samlor (Top Tables 2023 No. 14), has teamed up with Chef Jirapat “Sept” Praphotjanaporn of Nawa, to launch Kwann, a brand new project filled with Thai fine dining firewood delectables. Since the ingredients are mostly sourced from local producers across the regions, the menu is ever-evolving depending on the seasonal ingredients. The Thai Wagyu Beef Tartare with their jasmine rice charcoal crackers (B720) can make fans out of raw meat skeptics. It features diced Nong Khai tenderloin, tender but slightly chewy and subverts the gaminess with traditional herbs, leaning towards a mild zesty yum flavor. Above the fiery concept is the intention to have fun and experiment with varying ingredients. What you have on the first visit, might not be there in the next.','A vibrant dining spot, Kwann showcases Thai fine dining with a focus on seasonal ingredients sourced from local producers. Signature dishes include the Thai Wagyu Beef Tartare, which surprises with its fresh flavors and unique presentation. Expect an ever-changing menu that encourages culinary exploration and experimentation.','Thai,fine dining,seasonal ingredients',NULL,'{"openNow": false, "periods": [{"open": {"day": 0, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 0, "hour": 23, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 1, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 1, "hour": 23, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 2, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 2, "hour": 23, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 3, "hour": 18, "mi