INSERT INTO places VALUES(653,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/bendito-taco','<article>Bendito Taco</article>','2025-09-08 15:49:44.300515',13.718190799999998574,100.56396130000000432,'55 Rimthangrotfaisaipaknam Road, Khwaeng Khlong Toei, Khet Khlong Toei, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10110, Thailand','ChIJqaoNn0af4jARVtBtGlJAHBs','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJqaoNn0af4jARVtBtGlJAHBs','Bendito Taco','Restaurant','Ambitious bites at the new Bendito taco joint in Thonglor. Finally, a Mexican place with a Philly cheesesteak. It used to be difficult to get Mexican tacos in Bangkok, but now we’re spoiled for choice. A new place opened in Thonglor making some very bold menu choices for diners who want to indulge without breaking the bank. In the kitchen is Oscar Perez Garcia from Mexico City, who worked in the Mexico City Sheraton and Spain before finding his way to Bangkok. The venue is proud of the quality of their beef. If you’re a taco fanatic, get the beef on the Mexi Taco for the Australian slow cooked beef with bell peppers, coriander, and onion. The queso here is top-notch, and for dessert, absolutely do not forget the churros, which are exceptionally moist. While relying mainly on delivery in these days of Covid, the spot on Thonglor has a delightfully airy and kitschy desert vibe, good for a group setting.','A vibrant taco joint in Thonglor, offering bold Mexican flavors like the beef Mexi Taco with slow-cooked Australian beef. Known for its top-quality queso and moist churros, the space has a relaxed, kitschy vibe perfect for groups. With a focus on delivery during Covid, it caters to taco lovers seeking indulgent bites without overspending.','Mexican,Tacos,Casual Dining',NULL,NULL,'summarized',NULL,NULL,'2025-09-08 15:51:13',NULL,'CLOSED_TEMPORARILY',420,'gpt',2);
INSERT INTO places VALUES(654,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/yummz-kulfi','<article>Yummz Kulfi</article>','2025-09-08 15:49:44.301279',13.743670499999998124,100.50152249999999565,'อาคาร India Emporium 345 Chakkraphet Rd, Khwaeng Wang Burapha Phirom, Khet Phra Nakhon, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10200, Thailand','ChIJ1Y5u5QCZ4jARirDiKfwm74o','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJ1Y5u5QCZ4jARirDiKfwm74o','Yummz Kulfi','Restaurant','Indian sweet treats aren’t uncommon to Bangkok’s food scene (see our Indian sweet shop listings here), but Yummz Kulfi is arguably the first of its kind in Bangkok to dedicate itself entirely to these creamy, delicious no-churn ice creams. Even better? It’s affordable. The kulfi snacks here start at B60 for the smaller sizes, and the bigger ones go for around B70. Currently boasting 10 flavors, tastes range from the basic chocolate almond (B80) and crunchy pistachio (B70) to fancier bites like fresh saffron (B120).  If you’ve got a real hankering for kulfi you can pick out a combination of the 10 flavors for B580, available for delivery if Phahurat is a little out of your reach. Check their Facebook for pop-up events.  Saffron Kulfi (B120). Photo BK Magazine.Betel leaf kulfi (B70) with betel sweet nuts. Photo BK Magazine.','A unique spot in Bangkok, this venue specializes in creamy, no-churn kulfi ice creams with ten delightful flavors. Affordable prices start at B60, making it easy to indulge in favorites like saffron or pistachio. Perfect for a sweet treat, the option to mix flavors offers a fun experience for dessert lovers.','Indian,dessert,ice cream',NULL,'{"openNow": false, "periods": [{"open": {"day": 0, "hour": 10, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 0, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 2, "hour": 10, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 2, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 3, "hour": 10, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 3, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 4, "hour": 10, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 4, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 5, "hour": 10, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 5, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 6, "hour": 10, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 6, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}}], "weekdayDescriptions": ["Monday: Closed", "Tuesday: 10:30\u202fAM\u2009\u2013\u20096:00\u202fPM", "Wednesday: 10:30\u202fAM\u2009\u2013\u20096:00\u202fPM", "Thursday: 10:30\u202fAM\u2009\u2013\u20096:00\u202fPM", "Friday: 10:30\u202fAM\u2009\u2013\u20096:00\u202fPM", "Saturday: 10:30\u202fAM\u2009\u2013\u20096:00\u202fPM", "Sunday: 10:30\u202fAM\u2009\u2013\u20096:00\u202fPM"], "nextOpenTime": "2025-09-09T03:30:00Z"}','summarized',NULL,NULL,'2025-09-08 15:51:13',NULL,'OPERATIONAL',420,'gpt',2);
INSERT INTO places VALUES(655,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/hippo-dough','<article>Hippo Dough</article>','2025-09-08 15:49:44.302022',13.7378707000000011,100.5666031999999932,'Sawasdee, 245/14 ซ. สุขุมวิท 31 Khwaeng Khlong Toei Nuea, Watthana, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10110, Thailand','ChIJR-L_vBif4jARkqufm6_ILmI','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJR-L_vBif4jARkqufm6_ILmI','Hippo Dough','Restaurant','These are some fancy donuts. Hippo Dough is all about rich, decadent toppings, and the new shop on Sukhumvit Soi 31 uses ingredients from Europe and Thailand to create more than 100 impressive flavors. The creative twists, multi-layered frostings, and even fancy syringes make this shop a factory of unique flavors.  From classic, deluxe, and signature donuts and cheesecakes on a stick to milkshakes and craft sodas, there’s something for everyone. Keep it safe with the classic Nutella (B65), try the deluxe strawberry peanut butter (B120) for something nutty, and go all out with their signature Giotto dark chocolate (B150). Take it up a notch with a deluxe Kinder macaron cheesecake (B150) and wash it down with a classic vanilla milkshake (B150). Since the options here are endless, it’s probably best to visit the store to see which one catches your eye. If not, it''s available for delivery via Grab, Line, and Foodpanda. All images courtesy of Hippo Dough.','A vibrant spot for donut enthusiasts, this restaurant features over 100 unique flavors crafted with European and Thai ingredients. Specialty items include richly topped donuts, cheesecakes on a stick, and refreshing milkshakes. Perfect for sweet cravings, the menu offers creative twists that invite exploration.','desserts,donuts,sweets,cafes',NULL,NULL,'summarized',NULL,NULL,'2025-09-08 15:51:13',NULL,'CLOSED_PERMANENTLY',420,'gpt',2);
INSERT INTO places VALUES(656,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/ailati-resto','<article>Ailati Resto</article>','2025-09-08 15:49:44.302825',13.718819099999999266,100.51538889999998005,'1495 ถ. เจริญกรุง Si Lom, Khet Bang Rak, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10500, Thailand','ChIJy-Z1LcSY4jAR0VWo7W5y6Tc','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJy-Z1LcSY4jAR0VWo7W5y6Tc','Ailati Resto','Restaurant','The buzz: Just a stone’s throw from BTS Saphan Taksin, this charmingly low-key trattoria has attracted young-and-hip Instagrammers ever since opening in October last year. Ailati Resto is, however, not just Instagram bait. It’s a dining spot with an essence of Italy on point.   The vibe: Ailati ticks all the boxes for photogenic: abundance of natural light,  a stylish color combination, and rustic elements of dark wood, light walls and brick. Head early and pick a seat on the second floor for more privacy.  The food: Chef Antonio Cuppaiolo hand rolls his pasta and pizza dough fresh every day, and his menu—although straightforward—provides those homespun remedies we all need. On our last visit, we had his strozzapreti (B420) served with salsiccia (Italian sausage) and porcini and truffle sauce. The short, twisted pasta is coated with just the right amount of sauce—enough to dunk some bread once the dish is finished. And then there is his seafood tagliolini (B420), with thinly sliced ribbons tossed in a refreshingly light sauce accompanied by hefty prawns and tender squid. His quattro stagioni pizza (B380), meanwhile, has each quadrant generously filled with ham, mushroom, artichokes, and olives, offering a satisfying crunch to the crust. Like many Italian restaurants, Ailati also serves the staple tiramisu (B220) and excels at it: no soggy sponge and the mousse is not too sweet. But what we love more is the crema catalana (B180), a simple alchemy of egg, milk, and sugar that offers a jiggingly thick cream once you crack its outer caramelized layer.  Why we’d come back: Ailati promises a bevy of pizza variations—chef Cuppaiolo has six pages all dedicated to them—from the classic red and white to the sweet. It’s not all about Instagram. Photos: All rights reserved to Coconuts Media.','A cozy trattoria near BTS Saphan Taksin blends rustic charm with a vibrant atmosphere. Chef Antonio Cuppaiolo crafts fresh pasta and pizza daily, with standout dishes like seafood tagliolini and creamy crema catalana. Perfect for casual dining, the stylish space invites food lovers and Instagrammers alike.','Italian,Pasta,Pizza,Casual Dining','PRICE_LEVEL_MODERATE','{"openNow": false, "periods": [{"open": {"day": 0, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 0, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 1, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 1, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 2, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 2, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 3, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 3, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 4, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 4, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 5, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 5, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 6, "hour": 12, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 6, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}], "weekdayDescriptions": ["Monday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM", "Tuesday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM", "Wednesday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM", "Thursday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM", "Friday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM", "Saturday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM", "Sunday: 12:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fPM"], "nextOpenTime": "2025-09-09T05:00:00Z"}','summarized',NULL,NULL,'2025-09-08 15:51:13',NULL,'OPERATIONAL',420,'gpt',2);
INSERT INTO places VALUES(657,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/kates-place-supper-club','<article>Kate''s Place - Supper Club</article>','2025-09-08 15:49:44.303972',13.719015599999999643,100.57610479999998798,'38/1 Sukhumvit 36, Klongton, Khet Khlong Toei, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10110, Thailand','ChIJ-3Ss8cWf4jARit8xgGLTubg','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJ-3Ss8cWf4jARit8xgGLTubg','Kate''s Place - Supper Club','Restaurant','From experience at restaurants like Canvas and Suhring, Pikun “Kate” Wangsantia has now turned restaurateur with her very own fine-dining venture. It all started when Kate’s friends came down for a social visit and then word-of-mouth did the rest of the work. This supper club is set in an intimate space, hidden behind a bookshelf that looks like a stylish living room on the second floor of Kate’s shophouse.Kate’s Place aims to serve the staple Thai comfort food, a blend between traditional and fancy. The signature set menu (B990) here changes monthly and offers two starters, four shared courses, and a dessert. Think, beef panang with seasonal fruit, steamed red snapper with pickled lime, king pad prik manao, and more. If you’re looking for a private dining place, you can book out the entire place for 12 people.Make your bookings here or via Line @katesplacebkk All images courtesy of Kate''s Place.','An intimate supper club tucked behind a bookshelf offers a cozy vibe reminiscent of a stylish living room. The monthly changing set menu features elevated Thai comfort food, perfect for sharing with friends or celebrating special occasions. Ideal for private dining, the entire space can be booked for up to 12 guests.','supper club,Thai cuisine,fine dining,private dining',NULL,'{"openNow": false, "periods": [{"open": {"day": 0, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 0, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 2, "hour": 18, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 2, "hour": 22, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"da