INSERT INTO places VALUES(680,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/double-slash-rama-3','<article>Double Slash Rama 3</article>','2025-09-08 16:11:09.886281',13.701056599999998919,100.54064389999999296,'54 Thanon Naradhiwat Rajanagarindra, Khwaeng Chong Nonsi, Khet Yan Nawa, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10120, Thailand','ChIJP08Fsgyf4jAR-PkwvSGb0tk','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJP08Fsgyf4jAR-PkwvSGb0tk','Double Slash Rama 3','Restaurant','With its new branch on Rama 3, Double Slash draws inspiration from the striking Streamline Moderne movement, and the glass-fronted, all-white outpost is pulling in cafe-hoppers by the dozen.  The cafe gained a following with its first branch off Arun Amarin Road, near the Rama 8 bridge. At this branch, Double Slash still offers the quality artisanal coffee fans know and love, plus cold brew and more unique options. Oh, and that sleek design drawing queues each day. Try the black cold brew (B100), or go for a fancier drink, like the salted caramel with pink sea salt (B130) or Prachuap Dee (B120), coffee made with single-origin Prachuap Khiri Khan cacao. You can pair it all with pastries, like ham and cheese croissants (B125) and caneles (B85).   All images courtesy of Double Slash','A sleek, all-white café on Rama 3 showcases a design inspired by Streamline Moderne. Artisanal coffee lovers can enjoy unique options like salted caramel cold brew and single-origin chocolate drinks. Pastries complement the experience, making it a perfect spot for casual hangouts.','café,artisanal coffee,pastries',NULL,'{"openNow": false, "periods": [{"open": {"day": 0, "hour": 7, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 0, "hour": 17, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 1, "hour": 7, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 1, "hour": 17, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 2, "hour": 7, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 2, "hour": 17, "minute": 0}}, {"open": {"day": 3, "hour": 7, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 3, "hour": 17, "minute": 0}},