INSERT INTO places VALUES(686,'bk_magazine','https://bk.asia-city.com/restaurants/bangkok-restaurant-reviews/bloom-pretzel-and-coffee','<article>Bloom Pretzel and Coffee</article>','2025-09-08 16:11:09.890655',13.726726299999998381,100.65815730000000627,'16 ซอย พัฒนาการ 65 ประเวศ Khet Prawet, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10250, Thailand','ChIJF9nESk9hHTERt6Zd3qaXKIQ','https://maps.google.com/?cid=ChIJF9nESk9hHTERt6Zd3qaXKIQ','Bloom Pretzel and Coffee','Restaurant','This gray-walled cafe tucked away in Pattanakarn specializes in soft pretzels served fresh and hot each day, some with sweet or savory fillings that give a twist to the traditional German snack. Classic, knot-shaped soft pretzels come coated with French butter (B60) or roasted almonds (B75). You can also try their signature, ring-shaped stuffed pretzels, available in two flavors: 55% dark Belgian chocolate (B80) or the cream cheese-stuffed Queen Cheese (B85). The cafe also plans to experiment and release new flavors each month. The house coffee blends highlight local beans, like the medium-dark blend featuring Chiang Mai beans and the light-medium roast from Mae Taeng and Mae On (from B65 for an americano and B70 for a piccolo latte). Specialty and single-origin beans are also available.     All images courtesy of Bloom Pretzel and Coffee','A cozy cafe tucked away in Pattanakarn, soft pretzels are the star of the menu, featuring sweet and savory fillings. Specialty coffee blends highlight local beans, offering a delightful pairing with their signature treats. Monthly flavor experiments keep the offerings fresh and exciting.','cafe,pretzels,coffee','PRICE_LEVEL_MODERATE','{"openNow": false, "periods": [{"open": {"day": 0, "hour": 8, "minute": 30}, "close": {"day": 0, "hour": 17, "minute": 15}}, {"open": {"day": 1, "hour": 8, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 1, "hour": 16, "minute": 45}}, {"open": {"day": 2, "hour": 8, "minute": 0}, "close": {"day": 2, "hour": 16, "minute": 45}}, {"open": {"day": 3, "hour": 9, "min