jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310336/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310336/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310336/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310336/1536/1152/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310336/1920/1440/image.jpg 1920w" title="Big Dog Cafe" width="750"/></picture></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_18vpl_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photograph: Big Dog Cafe</span></figcaption></a></div><div class="_summaryContainer_osmln_364"><div class="_summary_osmln_21"><div class="_p_1mmxl_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The name says it all - Big Dog Cafe is the kingdom of kind giants. But it’s not just about their size; these hounds bring a rare and quirky charm you won’t find anywhere else. The cafe is home to more than 50 dogs from a wide variety of breeds - some familiar and others so unique you’ll hardly ever see them in Thailand. This is where we spot shaggy Komondors that look like walking rugs, friendly Alaskan Malamutes, fluffy Old English Sheepdogs, Airedale Terriers and of course, elegant Afghan Hounds that look like they just escaped a runway.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The cafe organises doggy playtime into five sessions a day, each featuring up to 10 different packs of dogs rotating in to meet visitors. That means every time you come, you’ll meet a new crew of furry friends. The space is roomy and welcoming, great for both grabbing a coffee break or settling in for a full meal while enjoying your unlimited dog cuddle time.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Entry starts at just B199 for adults (B150 for kids). If you’d like the full experience with drinks and dessert included, there’s a THB490 package or go all-in with the B590 package that also covers a meal.</span></p>\n<p><strong>358/21 Soi Ruam Nam, Khlong Chaokhun Sing, Wang Thonglang. Open Tue–Thu 9.30am–7.30pm (Closed Wed)</strong></p></div></div></div><div class="_ctaButtons_osmln_107"><div class="_cta_osmln_107 _viewMoreCta_osmln_128"><a class="_secondary_1gagn_22" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"action":"link - internal","category":"GP Engagement","label":"read more button"}}'' data-testid="view-more-cta_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/big-dog-cafe" rel="" target="_self"><span class="_textContent_1gagn_69">Read more</span></a></div></div></div></article><article class="tile _article_osmln_1" data-testid="tile-zone-large-list_testID"><div class="articleContent _articleContent_osmln_229"><div class="_title_osmln_9"><a class="" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/dog-country-cafe" rel="" target="_self"><h3 class="_h3_c6c0h_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Dog Country Cafe</h3></a></div><div class="_tileTags_osmln_50"><section class="_tags_1i2cm_17" data-testid="tags_testID"><ul class="_tagsList_1i2cm_17"><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Cafés</span></li><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Chatuchak</span></li></ul></section></div><div class="_imageContainer_osmln_46"><a class="tileImageLink" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/dog-country-cafe" rel="" target="_self"><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapDesktop_osmln_98"><picture><source height="422" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/400/225/image.webp 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/750/422/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1024/576/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1372/772/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1536/864/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1920/1080/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Dog Country Cafe" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-16-9" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="422" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/750/422/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/400/225/image.jpg 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/750/422/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1024/576/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1372/772/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1536/864/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1920/1080/image.jpg 1920w" title="Dog Country Cafe" width="750"/></picture></div><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapMobile_osmln_208"><picture><source height="562" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/380/285/image.webp 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/750/562/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1024/768/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1372/1029/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1536/1152/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1920/1440/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Dog Country Cafe" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-4-3" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="562" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/750/562/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1536/1152/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310337/1920/1440/image.jpg 1920w" title="Dog Country Cafe" width="750"/></picture></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_18vpl_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photograph: Dog Country Cafe</span></figcaption></a></div><div class="_summaryContainer_osmln_364"><div class="_summary_osmln_21"><div class="_p_1mmxl_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If we’re talking about the biggest dog cafe in Thailand, the crown goes to Dog Country Cafe. The space sprawls over three acres and is home to 400 dogs! The massive area is divided into several zones so you can pick your best playdate vibe.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Start at the Center Zone, where small and big dogs mingle in one lively playground. Next, head to the Tiny Paw Zone, designed for those who melt at pint-sized pups you can cuddle or feed unlimited treats. The Dog Gallery showcases medium-sized dogs, with a few fluffy models. Upstairs, things get wilder: rabbits, cats, goats and pigs add a petting zoo feel for extra fun.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And it’s not just about the four-legged friends. The cafe also comes with a dining area and live music stage, making it an all-day hangout spot for families and friends.</span></p>\n<p><strong>82, 39 Phutthamonthon Sai 2, Sala Thammasop, Thawi Watthana Open daily 9.30am–9pm. B300 (unlimited play in all zones and one free drink)</strong></p></div></div></div><div class="_ctaButtons_osmln_107"><div class="_cta_osmln_107 _viewMoreCta_osmln_128"><a class="_secondary_1gagn_22" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"action":"link - internal","category":"GP Engagement","label":"read more button"}}'' data-testid="view-more-cta_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/dog-country-cafe" rel="" target="_self"><span class="_textContent_1gagn_69">Read more</span></a></div></div></div></article><article class="tile _article_osmln_1" data-testid="tile-zone-large-list_testID"><div class="articleContent _articleContent_osmln_229"><div class="_title_osmln_9"><a class="" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/corgi-in-the-garden" rel="" target="_self"><h3 class="_h3_c6c0h_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Corgi in the Garden</h3></a></div><div class="_tileTags_osmln_50"><section class="_tags_1i2cm_17" data-testid="tags_testID"><ul class="_tagsList_1i2cm_17"><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Cafés</span></li><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Khlong San</span></li></ul></section></div><div class="_imageContainer_osmln_46"><a class="tileImageLink" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/corgi-in-the-garden" rel="" target="_self"><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapDesktop_osmln_98"><picture><source height="422" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/400/225/image.webp 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/750/422/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1024/576/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1372/772/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1536/864/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1920/1080/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Corgi in the Garden" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-16-9" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="422" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/750/422/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/400/225/image.jpg 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/750/422/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1024/576/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1372/772/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1536/864/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1920/1080/image.jpg 1920w" title="Corgi in the Garden" width="750"/></picture></div><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapMobile_osmln_208"><picture><source height="562" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/380/285/image.webp 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/750/562/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1024/768/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1372/1029/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1536/1152/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1920/1440/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Corgi in the Garden" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-4-3" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="562" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/750/562/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1536/1152/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310339/1920/1440/image.jpg 1920w" title="Corgi in the Garden" width="750"/></picture></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_18vpl_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photograph: Dog Country Cafe</span></figcaption></a></div><div class="_summaryContainer_osmln_364"><div class="_summary_osmln_21"><div class="_p_1mmxl_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For those who have already fallen for the charms of those round little corgi butts, Corgi in the Garden may well be your happy place. This cafe is home to 33 short-legged furballs, all waddling around like loaves of bread with tails. It all started when the owners, already corgi parents themselves, decided to share their joy by opening a space where everyone could experience the same fluffy happiness.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The cafe itself is cozy and cute, decorated like a warm garden home - best for snapping photos, sipping coffee or just chilling on a lazy afternoon. Corgis are famously playful, cheeky and extra cuddly so prepare to fall head over heels the moment you come in. On the menu you’ll find coffee, homemade pastries and ice cream - ideal for cooling down on a hot Bangkok day.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pro tip: go on a weekday if you want extra cuddle time. It’s less crowded, which means more corgi love for you.</span></p>\n<p><strong>240/1, Soi Charoen Nakhon 10, Khlong Ton Sai, Khlong San. Open daily 10am-6pm. B350 for adults, B450 for one drink and cake or ice cream, B250 for kids who are under 90-110 cm and free entry for kids under 90cm. </strong></p>\n</div></div></div><div class="_ctaButtons_osmln_107"><div class="_cta_osmln_107 _viewMoreCta_osmln_128"><a class="_secondary_1gagn_22" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"action":"link - internal","category":"GP Engagement","label":"read more button"}}'' data-testid="view-more-cta_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/corgi-in-the-garden" rel="" target="_self"><span class="_textContent_1gagn_69">Read more</span></a></div></div></div></article><article class="tile _article_osmln_1" data-testid="tile-zone-large-list_testID"><div class="articleContent _articleContent_osmln_229"><div class="_title_osmln_9"><a class="" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/dog-in-town-ari" rel="" target="_self"><h3 class="_h3_c6c0h_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Dog in Town Ari</h3></a></div><div class="_tileTags_osmln_50"><section class="_tags_1i2cm_17" data-testid="tags_testID"><ul class="_tagsList_1i2cm_17"><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Cafés</span></li><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Ari</span></li></ul></section></div><div class="_imageContainer_osmln_46"><a class="tileImageLink" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/dog-in-town-ari" rel="" target="_self"><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapDesktop_osmln_98"><picture><source height="422" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/400/225/image.webp 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/750/422/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1024/576/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1372/772/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1536/864/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1920/1080/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Dog in Town Ari" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-16-9" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="422" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/750/422/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/400/225/image.jpg 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/750/422/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1024/576/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1372/772/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1536/864/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1920/1080/image.jpg 1920w" title="Dog in Town Ari" width="750"/></picture></div><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapMobile_osmln_208"><picture><source height="562" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/380/285/image.webp 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/750/562/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1024/768/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1372/1029/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1536/1152/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1920/1440/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Dog in Town Ari" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-4-3" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="562" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/750/562/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1536/1152/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310341/1920/1440/image.jpg 1920w" title="Dog in Town Ari" width="750"/></picture></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_18vpl_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photograph: Dog in Town Ari</span></figcaption></a></div><div class="_summaryContainer_osmln_364"><div class="_summary_osmln_21"><div class="_p_1mmxl_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">From its first home in Ekkamai to its hipster-approved spot in Ari, Dog in Town Ari is a heaven if you’ve ever dreamed of hanging out with a crew of big, fluffy four-legged friends.  Siberian huskies, golden retrievers, corgis, a few cloud-like Samoyeds and a posse of smaller pups await you.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The cafe’s cutest gimmick is that every pup here is named after a BTS station. Don’t be surprised when you’re suddenly calling out ’On Nut’ or ‘Mo Chit’ while a giant ball of fur comes running your way.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The vibe is super laidback and friendly, like you’ve just dropped in to see friends who happen to have way better hair. Staff will help line you up for photos with the pups, some of whom are trained to pose like pros. You’re guaranteed to walk away with Instagram gold (and probably a new favorite station on the BTS line).</span></p>\n<p><strong>11/4 7 Phahonyothin Rd, Phaya Tha. Open daily 11am–8pm. Entry B350 for one drink</strong></p></div></div></div><div class="_ctaButtons_osmln_107"><div class="_cta_osmln_107 _viewMoreCta_osmln_128"><a class="_secondary_1gagn_22" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"action":"link - internal","category":"GP Engagement","label":"read more button"}}'' data-testid="view-more-cta_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/dog-in-town-ari" rel="" target="_self"><span class="_textContent_1gagn_69">Read more</span></a></div></div></div></article><article class="tile _article_osmln_1" data-testid="tile-zone-large-list_testID"><div class="articleContent _articleContent_osmln_229"><div class="_title_osmln_9"><a class="" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/neverland-husky" rel="" target="_self"><h3 class="_h3_c6c0h_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Neverland Husky</h3></a></div><div class="_tileTags_osmln_50"><section class="_tags_1i2cm_17" data-testid="tags_testID"><ul class="_tagsList_1i2cm_17"><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Cafés</span></li><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Phaya Thai</span></li></ul></section></div><div class="_imageContainer_osmln_46"><a class="tileImageLink" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/neverland-husky" rel="" target="_self"><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapDesktop_osmln_98"><picture><source height="422" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/400/225/image.webp 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/750/422/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1024/576/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1372/772/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1536/864/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1920/1080/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Neverland Husky" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-16-9" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="422" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/750/422/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/400/225/image.jpg 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/750/422/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1024/576/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1372/772/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1536/864/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1920/1080/image.jpg 1920w" title="Neverland Husky" width="750"/></picture></div><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapMobile_osmln_208"><picture><source height="562" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/380/285/image.webp 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/750/562/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1024/768/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1372/1029/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1536/1152/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1920/1440/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Neverland Husky" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-4-3" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="562" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/750/562/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1536/1152/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310342/1920/1440/image.jpg 1920w" title="Neverland Husky" width="750"/></picture></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_18vpl_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photograph: Neverland Husky</span></figcaption></a></div><div class="_summaryContainer_osmln_364"><div class="_summary_osmln_21"><div class="_p_1mmxl_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If fluffy dogs are your love language, then Neverland Husky is going to be your happy place. Picture this: more than 30 Siberian huskies, all groomed to perfection with cloud-soft fur that’s begging for cuddles. Sure, they’re big but every single one of them is gentle, goofy and totally people-friendly.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The real magic here is that you don’t just meet one or two but you get to dive right into the whole pack for playtime and group photos. And just when you think it can’t get any cuter, there are Akita Inus (rarely seen in Thailand) and the permanently-smiling Samoyeds waiting to steal your heart.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The cafe itself is styled like a spacious garden so you can actually run around and play with the dogs instead of being cooped up. Before heading out, wander through the souvenir corner where you’ll find paw-some merch and doggy-themed goodies to take home as a memory of your visit.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Soi Ari Samphan 2, Phaya Thai. Two sessions daily: 11am–2pm &amp; 3pm–6pm (time-limited).  Entry  B350–500 for one drink)</strong></p></div></div></div><div class="_ctaButtons_osmln_107"><div class="_cta_osmln_107 _viewMoreCta_osmln_128"><a class="_secondary_1gagn_22" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"action":"link - internal","category":"GP Engagement","label":"read more button"}}'' data-testid="view-more-cta_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/neverland-husky" rel="" target="_self"><span class="_textContent_1gagn_69">Read more</span></a></div></div></div></article><article class="tile _article_osmln_1" data-testid="tile-zone-large-list_testID"><div class="articleContent _articleContent_osmln_229"><div class="_title_osmln_9"><a class="" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/shibainu-story" rel="" target="_self"><h3 class="_h3_c6c0h_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Shibainu Story</h3></a></div><div class="_tileTags_osmln_50"><section class="_tags_1i2cm_17" data-testid="tags_testID"><ul class="_tagsList_1i2cm_17"><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Cafés</span></li><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Chula-Samyan</span></li></ul></section></div><div class="_imageContainer_osmln_46"><a class="tileImageLink" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/shibainu-story" rel="" target="_self"><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapDesktop_osmln_98"><picture><source height="422" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/400/225/image.webp 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/750/422/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1024/576/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1372/772/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1536/864/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1920/1080/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Shibainu Story" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-16-9" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="422" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/750/422/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/400/225/image.jpg 400w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/750/422/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1024/576/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1372/772/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1536/864/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1920/1080/image.jpg 1920w" title="Shibainu Story" width="750"/></picture></div><div class="_imageWrap_osmln_94 _imageWrapMobile_osmln_208"><picture><source height="562" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/380/285/image.webp 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/750/562/image.webp 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1024/768/image.webp 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1372/1029/image.webp 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1536/1152/image.webp 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1920/1440/image.webp 1920w" type="image/webp" width="750"/><img alt="Shibainu Story" class="_image_osmln_46 aspect-ratio-4-3" data-testid="responsive-image_testID" height="562" loading="lazy" sizes="auto" src="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/750/562/image.jpg" srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1536/1152/image.jpg 1536w,https://media.timeout.com/images/106310343/1920/1440/image.jpg 1920w" title="Shibainu Story" width="750"/></picture></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_18vpl_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photograph: Shibainu Story</span></figcaption></a></div><div class="_summaryContainer_osmln_364"><div class="_summary_osmln_21"><div class="_p_1mmxl_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shiba fans, this one’s for you. Shibainu Story is a cafe where the stars of the show are an entire pack of these cheeky, fluffy pups. You’ll meet everything from full-sized, bouncy Shibas to teeny-tiny puppies so cute they might just break your heart.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The cafe is smartly split into two zones: one for chilling with food and drinks and another that’s Shiba paradise, where the dogs roam free and are always ready to play. Shibas are famous for their playful (and slightly mischievous) personalities. So you can expect laughter or maybe a bit of headache. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Because Shibainu Story is also a Shiba farm, the experience doesn’t stop at cuddles and playtime. Fall for a pup here, and you might just be starting a whole new chapter with your very own Shiba companion.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Chula Soi 5, Banthat Thong Road, Dragon Town. Open daily 11am–10pm Entry B250 (no time limit)</strong></p></div></div></div><div class="_ctaButtons_osmln_107"><div class="_cta_osmln_107 _viewMoreCta_osmln_128"><a class="_secondary_1gagn_22" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"action":"link - internal","category":"GP Engagement","label":"read more button"}}'' data-testid="view-more-cta_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/shibainu-story" rel="" target="_self"><span class="_textContent_1gagn_69">Read more</span></a></div></div></div></article><article class="tile _article_osmln_1" data-testid="tile-zone-large-list_testID"><div class="articleContent _articleContent_osmln_229"><div class="_title_osmln_9"><a class="" data-data-layer=''{"triggerOn":0,"payload":{"category":"GP Engagement","label":"in content","action":"link - internal"}}'' data-testid="tile-link_testID" href="/bangkok/restaurants/bangkok-dog-cafe" rel="" target="_self"><h3 class="_h3_c6c0h_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Bangkok Dog Cafe</h3></a></div><div class="_tileTags_osmln_50"><section class="_tags_1i2cm_17" data-testid="tags_testID"><ul class="_tagsList_1i2cm_17"><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Cafés</span></li><li class="_tag_1i2cm_17"><span class="_text_1i2cm_68">Bang Khae</span></li></ul></section></div><div class="_imageContain